<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>YelpCamp 2023 - Edward Ding</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-GLhlTQ8iRABdZLl6O3oVMWSktQOp6b7In1Zl3/Jr59b6EGGoI1aFkw7cmDA6j6gD" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/home.css">
</head>
<body class = "d-flex text-center text-white bg-dark">
    <div class="cover-container d-flex w-100 h-100 p-3 mx-auto flex-column">
        <header class = "mb-auto">
            <div>
                <h3 class = "float-md-start mb-0">YelpCamp</h3>
                <nav class = "nav nav-masthead justify-content-center float-md-end">
                    <a class = "nav-link active" aria-current = "page "href="#">Home</a>
                    <a class = "nav-link" href="/campgrounds">Campgrounds</a>
                    <% if(!currentUser) { %>
                    <a class = "nav-link" href="/login">Login</a>
                    <a class = "nav-link" href="/register">Register</a>
                    <% } else { %>
                    <a class = "nav-link" href="/logout">Logout</a>
                    <% } %>
                </nav>
            </div>
        </header>
        <main class = "px-3">
            <h1>YelpCamp</h1>
            <p class = "lead"><br>Welcome to YelpCamp<br> This is a demo project, created by Edward Ding to learn and showcase my understanding of HTML, CSS, EJS, Bootstrap, JavaScript, MongoDB.
                Other technologies used include Node.js and Express.js. This web application has a set of campgrounds that are able to be created, read, updated, and deleted. Furthermore,
                each campground has reviews on them that are also able to created, read, used and deleted. Furthermore, the campgrounds are all geo-located on an interactive  cluster map.
                This web applications also enables authorization and both client side and serevr side authentication. 
                <br>Please feel free to take a look.<br>
            </p>
            <a href="/campgrounds" class="btn btn-large btn-secondary font-weight-bold text-white ">View Campgrounds</a>
        </main>
        <footer class = "mt-auto text-white-50">
            <p>&copy; 2023 Yelp Camp by Edward Ding</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-w76AqPfDkMBDXo30jS1Sgez6pr3x5MlQ1ZAGC+nuZB+EYdgRZgiwxhTBTkF7CXvN" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bs-custom-file-input/dist/bs-custom-file-input.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>